[TITLE]
PDA demand model combined with FAVAD leakage on the same pipe

A single reservoir feeding one junction. The junction has a demand that
is pressure-dependent (PDA), and the connecting pipe has FAVAD leakage.
This exercises the interaction between PDA demand reduction and pipe
leakage, both of which modify the demand residual in the GGA solver.

[JUNCTIONS]
;ID      Elev   Demand
J1       50     100

[RESERVOIRS]
;ID      Head
R1       200

[PIPES]
;ID  Node1  Node2  Length  Diam  Roughness  MinorLoss  Status
P1   R1     J1     1000    12    100        0          Open

[LEAKAGE]
;Pipe  Coeff1  Coeff2
P1     50      0.1

[OPTIONS]
Units                GPM
Headloss             H-W
Demand Model         PDA
Minimum Pressure     0
Required Pressure    30
Pressure Exponent    0.5

[END]
